    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Assaf-Harofeh Medical Center</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The methods of detoxification under general anesthesia have been criticized because of
      limited data on safety and long-term follow-up. Premedication with buprenorphine has been
      advocated to improve safety. In current study we want to evaluate the importance of
      buprenorphine preparation in rapid opioid detoxification process, under general anesthesia.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
